      • onBackPressed

        public void onBackPressed()
        This has a lot of code in common with saveConfiguration. This is apparently the only way to do this, because of the way the onClickListener accesses the "final EditText input". I modularized as much as I could but this was as far as I got. Note that onBackPressed has to have a finish() once you click the "OK" button or the back button won't actually go back.

      • saveConfiguration

        public void saveConfiguration(View v)
        A button-specific method, this gets called when you click the "writeXML" button. This writes the current objects into an XML file located in the Configuration File Directory. The user is prompted for the name of the file.
        Parameters:
        v - the View from which this was called
